# BFF (GraphQL Mesh) Acceptance Criteria
# ADR-046: GraphQL Mesh with DSL-embedded configuration
# REQ-BFF-001..004 summarized as GWT scenarios

Feature: BFF build, dev, and validation from DSL data section
  As a developer
  I want the BFF to be generated and served from the DSL
  So teams don't handcraft Mesh config and can run quickly

  Background:
    Given the CLI is available as `seans-mfe-tool`
    And a project with `mfe-manifest.yaml`

  Scenario: Build Mesh config from DSL (happy path)
    Given `mfe-manifest.yaml` contains a `data:` section with at least one source
    And the source defines `handler.openapi.source: ./specs/petstore.yaml`
    When I run `seans-mfe-tool bff:build --manifest mfe-manifest.yaml`
    Then `.meshrc.yaml` is generated in the project root
    And a `.mesh/` directory is created with build artifacts

  Scenario: Dev server with hot reload
    Given `.meshrc.yaml` is present or can be generated from the manifest
    When I run `seans-mfe-tool bff:dev --manifest mfe-manifest.yaml`
    Then the GraphQL endpoint serves at `http://localhost:4000/graphql`
    And changes to the `data:` section are reflected without restart

  Scenario: Validate configuration without building
    Given `mfe-manifest.yaml` contains a `data:` section
    When I run `seans-mfe-tool bff:validate --manifest mfe-manifest.yaml`
    Then the command exits successfully for valid sources
    And shows errors if sources are missing or malformed

  Scenario: Missing data section (error path)
    Given `mfe-manifest.yaml` does not contain `data:`
    When I run `seans-mfe-tool bff:build --manifest mfe-manifest.yaml`
    Then the command fails with an error containing "No GraphQL configuration found in DSL"

  Scenario: Invalid source URL (error path)
    Given the `data:` section has a source with an unreachable `handler.openapi.source`
    When I run `seans-mfe-tool bff:validate --manifest mfe-manifest.yaml`
    Then validation fails with the specific source name
    And suggests checking network or endpoint availability

  Scenario: Serve configuration in DSL
    Given the `data:` section defines `serve.endpoint: /graphql` and `serve.playground: true`
    When I run `seans-mfe-tool bff:dev`
    Then the server responds to introspection query at `/graphql`
    And the GraphQL Playground is accessible
