## REQ-BFF-006: Production Plugins

### Scenario: Response cache plugin configured
```gherkin
Given a data.plugins section with responseCache
When the user runs `mfe bff:build`
Then .meshrc.yaml includes the responseCache plugin
  And the ttl value is preserved
```

### Scenario: Rate limit plugin configured
```gherkin
Given a data.plugins section with rateLimit
When the user runs `mfe bff:build`
Then .meshrc.yaml includes the rateLimit plugin
  And the configuration is preserved
```

---

## REQ-BFF-007: Transforms for Schema Shaping

### Scenario: Prefix transform applied
```gherkin
Given a source with prefix transform value "User_"
When mesh build completes
Then GraphQL types are prefixed with "User_"
  And Query fields are prefixed with "User_"
```

### Scenario: FilterSchema removes fields
```gherkin
Given a source with filterSchema excluding "Query.!internal*"
When mesh build completes
Then internal queries are not exposed in GraphQL schema
```

---

## REQ-BFF-008: Discovery and Introspection

### Scenario: Introspection enabled by default
```gherkin
Given a running BFF server
When a client sends GraphQL introspection query
Then the full schema is returned
```

### Scenario: Playground available in development
```gherkin
Given serve.playground is true in configuration
When the user navigates to /graphql in browser
Then GraphiQL or Mesh playground is displayed
```

